Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

685a6450-186e-40c5-aa1c-4b8996082d9e.d60f6bbc-a0dc-4b31-a5d9-71f0e9cc2bf5.callout=get UUID for flowName 685a6450-186e-40c5-aa1c-4b8996082d9e.description=
Synopsis

    This flow wraps low-level HPOO getters and then makes a list of clusters available for consumption by future groups.
    callAtlasGetterByClusterNames performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve the UUID for the provided flow NAME\: $getterOperation.
      2. Get the required inputs based on the UUID/getterOperation.
      3. Iterate through clusters\: load inputs, launch the getterOperation, and then document either the success and output or the failure.
      4. Output all pass and failed clusters, outputs, or both.
      5. Respond with Unknown for any failed flows.

Inputs

    getterOperation - Low-level command found in (/Library/HostingEngineering/Library/StorageFlows/NetApp) -- getUUID -- to run publicly against all clusterNames (required).
	Valid Values\:
	Default Value\:

    clusterNames - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster.
	Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
	Default value\: None.
	  
    <*> - Any and all other loaded inputs, will be "overloaded* and used by the getterOperation called. Example would be siteID
	Valid values\: Valid inputs to the target flow, and inputs.
	Default value\: None.

Results

    callAtlasGettersOutput - Output of target flow (getterOperation)

Responses

    Success - Ran against all clusterNames successfully, returns cluster-aware data from each NetApp.
    Failure - Failure to run getterOperation against clusterName.
    Unknown - Return Non-Zero\: Most cases for issue with one or more clusterNames connectivity and retrieval, or couldnt find UUID of getterOperation.

Notes

     1. Example Input from Cordys\:

         
            atlas
            48ec1fba-b861-4be4-b44a-279bfeec8e3c
            false
            
                
                  getterOperation
                  blah
                  
                
                  clusterNames
                  10.12.60.7
                  
                
                  siteId
                  S1110
